Many of the people who live in Whitminster do not work in the village or on the surrounding farms. The people who live on the new estates either travel up the road to Gloucester to work, which takes about fifteen minutes, or some go down to Bristol, which takes about half an hour on the motorway. However, there are local employment opportunities and we surveyed the main local employers. These were:
{ATTWOOLLS}
This company are a specialist tent making and erecting business. John Attwooll first started a business making medicines for vets, then he set up an apple collecting business when this area used to be a big cider producing area. Cont. on page 15.
